From Subject Re mazda just does not feel right In article Ram Mohan writes I've a mazda with about miles on Recently I do not get a good feeling of the road on a wet pavement when driving the It feels as if the car is wandering and there is no grip on the The tires are the original ones and have threads on them passes the penny head test I had the shocks and struts and alignment checked and things are However I feel like that I dont have the grip of the road and feel as if the car is wandering on Any help in this is Two shots at it Check the tires again if you can see the wear bars you're down to problem area and some tires pass a penny test between the bars that's no guide at all Your problem in the wet is call You may not have enough tread left to channel water out from under the tire so it goes fishy on you as it lifts off the Tires In particular soft tire compounds get harder as you put them thru more heat Harder compounds don't grip as well as soft Effect is very noticable on tires that get very hot very often such as in competition but it hits all Bob Benson